---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="About — The Great Stabbing">
  <section class="px-6 py-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto prose">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">About</h1>
    <p class="text-stone">
      The Great Stabbing is a Europe-wide, open-source map and dashboard of violent
      crime. It pulls statistics from each country's official authority (BKA in
      Germany, data.police.uk in the UK, SSMSI in France, BRÅ in Sweden, Danmarks
      Statistik in Denmark, Ministerio del Interior in Spain, ISTAT in Italy) and
      adds an incident-level news layer extracted monthly from European media.
    </p>
    <p class="text-stone mt-4">
      The project is solo-built, open-source, and methodologically strict. Every
      figure links to its official source. Gaps are shown as gaps, never imputed.
    </p>
    <p class="text-stone mt-4">
      Inspired by <a href="https://hoyodecrimen.com">hoyodecrimen.com</a>, a Mexico
      City crime data project that this borrows its spirit and pipeline ideas from.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
